<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Development Server on cem</title><link>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/</link><description>Recent content in Development Server on cem</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Getting Started</title><link>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/getting-started/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/getting-started/</guid><description>&lt;p>This guide will walk you through setting up &lt;code>cem serve&lt;/code> for your custom element project.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Before using &lt;code>cem serve&lt;/code>, you need:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Custom elements manifest&lt;/strong> - Generate one with 
&lt;a href="https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/commands/generate/">&lt;code>cem generate&lt;/code>
&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Demo files&lt;/strong> - HTML files in &lt;code>demo/&lt;/code> directories or named &lt;code>*.demo.html&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="the-workflow">The Workflow&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;code>cem serve&lt;/code> follows a manifest-driven development workflow:&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Write your component&lt;/strong> with JSDoc documentation&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Generate manifest&lt;/strong> with &lt;code>cem generate&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Add demos&lt;/strong> in &lt;code>demo/&lt;/code> directories (automatically discovered)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Run serve&lt;/strong> with &lt;code>cem serve&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Iterate&lt;/strong> - edit, test, and changes trigger live reload&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="1-install-cem">1. Install cem&lt;/h3>

&lt;code-highlighter>
 &lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">npm install --save-dev @pwrs/cem&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>
&lt;/code-highlighter>&lt;h3 id="2-generate-a-manifest">2. Generate a manifest&lt;/h3>

&lt;code-highlighter>
 &lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">cem generate&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>
&lt;/code-highlighter>&lt;p>This creates &lt;code>custom-elements.json&lt;/code> with your component metadata.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Rendering Modes</title><link>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/rendering-modes/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/rendering-modes/</guid><description>&lt;p>The dev server supports three rendering modes for serving demos, allowing you to choose the right environment for your workflow.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="light-mode-default">Light Mode (Default)&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Full development UI with all features enabled. This is the standard mode for component development.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Features:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>PatternFly-based UI with sidebar navigation&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Header with branding, theme toggle, and debug info&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Interactive knobs for attributes, properties, and CSS custom properties&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Real-time event monitoring tab&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Server logs viewer with filtering&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Manifest browser&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Live reload with visual connection status&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Error overlays for transform failures&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Usage:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Buildless Development</title><link>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/buildless/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/buildless/</guid><description>&lt;p>Write TypeScript and import CSS directly in your browser - no build step required. &lt;code>cem serve&lt;/code> lets you develop without running &lt;code>tsc&lt;/code>, CSS watchers, or bundlers.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="write-typescript-directly">Write TypeScript Directly&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Import TypeScript files directly in your demos without compilation:&lt;/p>

&lt;code-highlighter>
 &lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-html" data-lang="html">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="c">&amp;lt;!-- In your demo --&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">script&lt;/span> &lt;span class="na">type&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;module&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="na">src&lt;/span>&lt;span class="o">=&lt;/span>&lt;span class="s">&amp;#34;../src/my-element.ts&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">script&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
&lt;/code-highlighter>&lt;p>No need to:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Run &lt;code>tsc --watch&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Set up a build pipeline&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Wait for compilation before testing&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Manage separate source and output directories&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>The dev server handles TypeScript on-demand with full source map support for debugging.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Knobs</title><link>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/knobs/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://bennypowers.dev/cem/docs/serve/knobs/</guid><description>&lt;p>Knobs are interactive controls that let you test your custom elements by manipulating their attributes, properties, and CSS custom properties in real-time.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="how-knobs-work">How Knobs Work&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Knobs are automatically generated from your &lt;strong>Custom Elements Manifest&lt;/strong>. The dev server reads your component&amp;rsquo;s API documentation and creates appropriate controls for each attribute, property, and CSS variable.&lt;/p>
